Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @smoked paprika{2%tsp} in a #mixing bowl{} with the @honey{2%tbsp} and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} and mix together. Add the @chicken thighs{8} to the bowl and rub the flavourings into the meat. Remember to wash your hands afterwards!

Chop the @potato{2} into wedges the size of your index finger (no need to peel!). Put on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a splash of @oil{splash}. Sprinkle on half the @dried thyme{1%tsp}, season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} and toss to coat. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, then remove the core from the @yellow pepper{2}(halved) and slice into 1cm wide strips. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{2} into 2cm pieces.

Put the pepper and onion on another baking tray and sprinkle over the remaining @dried thyme{1%tsp}. Place the chicken on top and roast on the top shelf of your oven until the veggies are soft and the chicken is cooked, ~{20-25%mins}. The chicken skin should be slightly scorched as well for extra flavour!

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{2} (stalks and all). There should be time now to do the washing up or just relax for a little while!

Set the chicken aside for a moment. Sprinkle half the parsley on the pepper and onion and toss to combine. Serve the veggies on plates with the chicken thighs on top and the chips to the side. Drizzle over any remaining juices from your #baking tray{} and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley and a dollop of @mayonnaise{4%dollops}. Enjoy!